<!-- FAQ Section -->
<section id="faq" class="faq-section section">
	<div class="container">
		<h2 class="section-title">FAQ</h2>
		<p class="section-intro">Answers to common questions about configuring and running AI workflows with Eleoro.</p>
		<div class="faq-list">
			<div class="faq-item">
				<div class="faq-question">How do I know which workflows I need?<span class="faq-toggle-icon">+</span></div>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					We start with a short call to map your processes; such as handling leads, managing orders, or
					automating follow-ups. Based on that, we recommend a small set of pre-built workflows that match your tools
					(like HubSpot, Shopify, or QuickBooks). Each workflow can later be customized as your workflows evolve.
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="faq-item">
				<div class="faq-question">How fast will I see results?<span class="faq-toggle-icon">+</span></div>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					Most small-business clients launch their first workflows within 4–8 weeks. Pilot results; such as reduced
					manual tasks or faster response times; are usually visible within the first 30 days of deployment. Larger
					enterprise projects may include extended testing and approval phases.
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="faq-item">
				<div class="faq-question">Do I need any technical skills?<span class="faq-toggle-icon">+</span></div>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					No technical background is required. eleoro handles setup, integration, and testing on your preferred
					platforms. Once live, you'll have access to an intuitive dashboard where you can monitor activity and
					request changes with a single click.
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="faq-item">
				<div class="faq-question">Is it secure?<span class="faq-toggle-icon">+</span></div>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					Yes. Your data stays within the platforms you already use. We build on trusted tools like OpenAI's Agent
					Builder, Zapier, Make, n8n, and Workato; each offering enterprise-grade encryption, audit logs, and SOC 2 or
					GDPR compliance. Eleoro does not store or retain customer data.
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="faq-item">
				<div class="faq-question">Can I start small and expand later?<span class="faq-toggle-icon">+</span></div>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					Absolutely. Most clients begin with one or two workflows, such as a Follow-Up or Orders workflow, and add
					more as
					they see results. Because every workflow runs on modular integrations, scaling to additional workflows or
					departments is straightforward and low-risk.
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="faq-item">
				<div class="faq-question">Which tools and platforms do you support?<span class="faq-toggle-icon">+</span>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					We integrate with major business systems including HubSpot, Salesforce, Shopify, QuickBooks, Google
					Workspace, and Slack; plus over 5,000 apps supported by Zapier, Make, n8n, and Workato. During setup, we
					confirm compatibility and provide documentation for your exact tech stack.
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="faq-item">
				<div class="faq-question">What happens after launch?<span class="faq-toggle-icon">+</span></div>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					After deployment, you'll receive a 30-day performance review to ensure your workflows meet expected
					outcomes.
					We also offer optional monthly health checks and updates to keep automations aligned with your evolving
					processes.
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="faq-item">
				<div class="faq-question">Can you help with compliance or legal documentation?<span
				class="faq-toggle-icon">+</span></div>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					We provide a Data Processing Agreement (DPA) template for review and reference. Formal legal approval should
					be completed by your counsel. All connected platforms maintain published compliance certifications and can
					provide their respective reports on request.
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

